{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" if any of the tests in the bitfield "},{"code":"test","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". For example, ","type":"text"},{"code":"(G_FILE_TEST_EXISTS | G_FILE_TEST_IS_DIR)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will return ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" if the file exists; the check whether it’s a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"directory doesn’t matter since the existence test is "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". With","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the current set of available tests, there’s no point passing in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"more than one test at a time."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/filetest(filename:test:)"]}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:4GLib8fileTest8filename4testSbSPys4Int8VGSg_AA04FileC0VtF","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"fileTest(filename:test:)","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"fileTest","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"filename","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">!, "},{"text":"test","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"FileTest","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib8FileTestV"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"symbolKind":"func","roleHeading":"Function"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fileTest"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"filename"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">!, "},{"text":"test","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/FileTest","text":"FileTest","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib8FileTestV"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apart from "},{"code":"isSymlink","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" all tests follow symbolic links,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"so for a symbolic link to a regular file "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_file_test()"},{"text":" will return","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" for both "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isSymlink"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"isRegular","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note, that for a dangling symbolic link "},{"code":"g_file_test()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will return"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" for ","type":"text"},{"code":"isSymlink","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for all other flags."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You should never use "},{"code":"g_file_test()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to test whether it is safe"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to perform an operation, because there is always the possibility"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the condition changing before you actually perform the operation,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"see "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time-of-check_to_time-of-use","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, you might think you could use "},{"code":"isSymlink","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to know whether it is safe to write to a file without being"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"tricked into writing into a different location. It doesn’t work!"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":[" \/\/ DON'T DO THIS"," if (!g_file_test (filename, G_FILE_TEST_IS_SYMLINK))","   {","     fd = g_open (filename, O_WRONLY);","     \/\/ write to fd","   }",""," \/\/ DO THIS INSTEAD"," fd = g_open (filename, O_WRONLY | O_NOFOLLOW | O_CLOEXEC);"," if (fd == -1)","   {","     \/\/ check error","     if (errno == ELOOP)","       \/\/ file is a symlink and can be ignored","     else","       \/\/ handle errors as before","   }"," else","   {","     \/\/ write to fd","   }"],"syntax":"C","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Another thing to note is that "},{"code":"exists","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isExecutable"},{"type":"text","text":" are implemented using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"access()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"system call. This usually doesn’t matter, but if your program","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is setuid or setgid it means that these tests will give you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the answer for the real user ID and group ID, rather than the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"effective user ID and group ID."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On Windows, there are no symlinks, so testing for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isSymlink"},{"text":" will always return ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Testing for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isExecutable"},{"text":" will just check that the file exists and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"its name indicates that it is executable, checking for well-known"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"extensions and those listed in the "},{"code":"PATHEXT","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" environment variable."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/fileTest(filename:test:)"},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/FileTest":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/FileTest","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"FileTest","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"FileTest","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/filetest","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"FileTest","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A test to perform on a file using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_file_test()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time-of-check_to_time-of-use":{"identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time-of-check_to_time-of-use","title":"TOCTOU","type":"link","url":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time-of-check_to_time-of-use","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"TOCTOU","type":"text"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/fileTest(filename:test:)":{"title":"fileTest(filename:test:)","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fileTest"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"filename"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"test","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib8FileTestV","text":"FileTest","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/fileTest(filename:test:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" if any of the tests in the bitfield "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"test"},{"type":"text","text":" are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". For example, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(G_FILE_TEST_EXISTS | G_FILE_TEST_IS_DIR)"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will return ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if the file exists; the check whether it’s a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"directory doesn’t matter since the existence test is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":". With"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the current set of available tests, there’s no point passing in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"more than one test at a time."}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/filetest(filename:test:)"}}}